Press Releases.Title: No New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 23 January 2021, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed that there are no new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection.
 
2.      There are 10 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.
 
3.      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.
 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
23 JANUARY 2021
